OL,7,F"We saw it in the Stormont chamber on
OL,8,FMonday, and even at Westminster
OL,9,Fyesterday, just how much he was
OL,10,Frespected by politicians on all sides.
OL,12,F"There was harmony at Stormont on
OL,13,FMonday and we all know how rare that
OL,14,Fis.
OL,16,F"If it catches on, many of us in this
OL,17,Fchurch will be out of a job soon."
OL,19,FMr Simpson said despite Mr Reid's
OL,20,Fprofessional achievements, he was a
OL,21,F"family man first and foremost".
